        <p>The 21st century has seen the definitive shift from a unipolar world, dominated solely by the United States, to a multipolar system. Emerging powers like China, India, and Brazil are exerting growing influence over global economics and international diplomacy. This transition creates both new opportunities for cooperation and new arenas for competition, fundamentally altering the global balance of power.</p>
